The paper discusses the security of machine learning models, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses adversarial attacks and the need for dynamic and reactive approaches, which are relevant to "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the importance of detecting changes in data distribution, which is relevant to "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS).
